article.headline: Austin Peay 87, Tennessee Tech 71
article.story: EDs: APNewsNow. Austin Peay 87, Tennessee Tech 71. CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Wes Channels scored 28 points to lead Austin Peay to an 87-71 victory over Tennessee Tech on Thursday night. Drake Reed added 23 points for the Governors (11-7, 7-1 Ohio Valley Conference), who won their fifth consecutive game. Austin Peay led 37-27 at halftime and increased its lead to 64-40 with 10:36 remaining in the game. The Governors shot 53.4 percent from the floor (31 of 58) and hit nine 3-pointers. Tennessee Tech (9-9, 3-5) hit 11 3-pointers but never challenged in the second half. Channels was 8 of 9 from the line. Anthony Campbell added 12 points and Marcel Williams had 10 rebounds for Austin Peay. Daniel Northern had 12 points and 12 rebounds for Tennessee Tech. Will Barnes, who hit all four of his 3-point attempts, scored 12 points and Alex Davis added 10 points.
